{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Improve safety for E-Bikes and E-Scooters to reduce injuries",
        "additional_details": "E-bikes & e-scooters must be made safer in UK towns and cities. At present, children as young as 14 can ride heavy, powerful bikes, which are often poorly maintained, without helmets, while rental firms\u2019 18+ limits are often poorly enforced. Riders use them at night, sometimes after drinking or drug use, at speeds fast enough to kill or cause life-changing injuries. Without swift action, preventable deaths and life-changing injuries will continue to rise. The law is not keeping up with their use.",
        "background": "\u2022 Make helmets mandatory\r\n\u2022 Introduce drink/drug limits, with enforceable testing powers\r\n\u2022 Raise minimum age FOR USE to 18\r\n\u2022 Cap rental e-bike/scooter speeds at 12 mph nationwide\r\n\u2022 Require safety inspections and minimum maintenance standards\r\n\u2022 Strengthen penalties against dangerous riding",
